  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing Address Registration</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must register your Hungarian address within 30 days of arrival. This is a legal requirement—don't skip it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insufficient Insurance Documentation</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Your insurance certificate must clearly show €30,000+ coverage, repatriation, and full duration. Generic travel insurance will be rejected.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Unclear Income Proof</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">If income comes from multiple sources, provide clear documentation for each. Bank statements alone may not be sufficient—include contracts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Collecting Physical Card</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must visit a regional directorate to collect your physical residence card after arrival. This isn't optional.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Easy Renewal Beyond 2 Years</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The White Card is renewable once for a maximum of 2 years total. It's not a path to permanent residency—plan accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Assuming English Everywhere</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">English is common in Budapest's expat areas but limited elsewhere. Government offices especially may require Hungarian—bring a translator if needed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

