  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I work for Hungarian clients on the White Card?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. The White Card specifically requires work for non-Hungarian employers or clients. Working for Hungarian companies requires different permits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I travel in the Schengen Area?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Hungary is a Schengen member. Your White Card allows travel throughout the 27-country Schengen zone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What if I have variable income?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Use the savings option. Show €6,000+ in your bank account instead of monthly income proof. This is perfect for freelancers with irregular earnings.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How's the internet in Budapest?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Excellent. Hungary has widespread fiber optic coverage. Most apartments have 100+ Mbps, and coworking spaces are plentiful with reliable connections.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I bring my family?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Family members can apply for their own residence permits. They'll need to demonstrate their relationship to you and meet their own financial requirements.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I convert to permanent residency?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The White Card isn't a direct path to permanent residency. After 2 years, you'd need to explore other residence permit options if you want to stay longer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

